SIMPLE: ophthalmoscope
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ophthalmoscope
<hw>Oph*thal"mo*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From Gr.
<grk>'ofqalmo`s</grk> the eye + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An instrument for viewing the interior of the
eye, particularly the retina. Light is thrown into the eye by a mirror
(usually concave) and the interior is then examined with or without the
aid of a lens.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Oph*thal`mo*scop"ic</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ophthalmoscopy</ent>⟦br⟧
